Which do you think looks better?

15
00:02:26,099 --> 00:02:33,519
Jiang Qiao Xi, what's wrong?
Why aren't you talking?

16
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:40,540
Didn't you tell me I should express my feelings
and rely on you more?

17
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,340
Fine. What do you want then?

18
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:52,180
How about you pick one?
I'll get it for you. What about this pair?

19
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:55,099
I don't want sunglasses. I want something else.

20
00:02:55,099 --> 00:02:57,400
What else do you want?

21
00:02:57,400 --> 00:03:03,739
Alright. After buying sunglasses, we'll still
have 6-7k left. Pick whatever you want.

22
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:15,820
Let me buy Yu Qiao's sunglasses.
I actually want to give him a gift.

23
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:18,780
Why?

24
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:22,360
Last time Yu Qiao came to Hong Kong,
he said some things to me.

25
00:03:23,139 --> 00:03:28,180
Factually speaking, he's spent more time
with you than I have.

26
00:03:28,180 --> 00:03:32,560
Maybe he really understands you better than I do.

27
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:35,679
Why... why are you saying such weird things?

28
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:44,959
I just want to say thank you.
Cherry, you never gave up on me.

29
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,380
Don't talk like that anymore.

30
00:03:57,020 --> 00:04:03,580
Actually, Yu Qiao considers you a friend.
He's also worried about you.

31
00:04:03,580 --> 00:04:08,240
You know what? He's the one who found me
and gave me your Hong Kong address.

32
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:14,439
Without him, finding you
would've been much harder.

33
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:18,100
So I should thank him too.

34
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:26,199
You two are so similar.
Both of you want others to be happy.

35
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,900
Check this out.

36
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,960
Looks good.

37
00:04:39,160 --> 00:04:41,600
Do you want me to go back to Hong Yang to study?

38
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,800
What do you mean?

39
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,920
Nothing. Just thinking out loud.

40
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:59,579
Want to buy something? We won big.
Shouldn't we spend some?

41
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:08,060
I've thought it through.
I want to buy Ruo Cheng some plants.

42
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:11,759
Having plants at home after discharge
will lift his mood.

43
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:14,500
I also want to get Ya Lin some fine wine.

44
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:17,120
Shouldn't we celebrate properly
when Ruo Cheng gets discharged?

45
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,579
And Rui Rui, right?

46
00:05:19,579 --> 00:05:22,339
Let's buy Rui Rui some toys and new clothes.

47
00:05:22,339 --> 00:05:25,019
And your uncle and aunt, I think they...

48
00:05:25,019 --> 00:05:27,620
Haven't you thought
about getting something for yourself?

49
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:31,480
Ruo Cheng and Ya Lin told me
to shop more with you.

50
00:05:32,319 --> 00:05:34,720
What? Buying lipstick and heels?

51
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:37,120
That works too.

52
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,160
I don't need lipstick. I'm pretty enough.

53
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,959
I don't need heels. I'm tall enough.

54
00:05:41,959 --> 00:05:43,759
Let me stand here.

55
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:49,620
Listen, those things mean nothing to me.

56
00:05:49,620 --> 00:05:53,059
They only matter because they're from you.

57
00:05:55,980 --> 00:06:00,900
Cherry, you're so wonderful.
It makes me not want to let you go.

58
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:09,119
Your reluctance won't change anything.
I'm leaving the day after tomorrow.

59
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:13,639
I know.

60
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:20,899
So let's make the most of
our time shopping. Don't be upset.

61
00:06:20,899 --> 00:06:23,759
Let's visit Ruo Cheng and Ya Lin tonight.

62
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:24,819
Okay.

63
00:06:24,819 --> 00:06:27,619
Okay, I have something to discuss with them.

64
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,939
Ya Lin, we're here!

65
00:07:08,939 --> 00:07:11,459
Come in!

66
00:07:11,459 --> 00:07:12,639
Ya Lin.

67
00:07:12,639 --> 00:07:17,819
Ya Lin, you look absolutely stunning today.

68
00:07:17,819 --> 00:07:21,060
That's our Cherry! Thank you.

69
00:07:21,060 --> 00:07:22,980
Let me through.

70
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:26,220
- Money tree!
- A money tree. Thank you.

71
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:27,800
Auntie, Uncle.

72
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:30,699
- Uncle, I got you supplements.
- Ruo Cheng.

73
00:07:30,699 --> 00:07:32,319
I'll stay seated.

74
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:34,259
- Cheers!
- Soup for wine.

75
00:07:34,259 --> 00:07:35,680
Cherry, thank you for the wine.

76
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,480
Thank you.

77
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:42,939
You really won the lottery? Over 9,000?

78
00:07:42,939 --> 00:07:45,759
Yeah, never expected to actually win.

79
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:49,759
You were right, Cherry. People should have hope.

80
00:07:49,759 --> 00:07:55,500
Let me say this, Qiao Xi, thank you
for your hard work these two years.

81
00:07:55,500 --> 00:08:00,560
Thank you, and everyone's care
for me hasn't been easy.

82
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:03,160
Especially my wife.

83
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,279
No need to say all that.

84
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:09,639
It's necessary. I still have
some old debts to collect.

85
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:13,879
Though collecting them now won't be easy,

86
00:08:13,879 --> 00:08:19,319
if I go personally,
they'll at least show some respect.

87
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:25,519
No big issue. So our family matters are settled.

88
00:08:25,519 --> 00:08:29,839
Therefore, Qiao Xi, quit all your part-time jobs.

89
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:33,952
I've noticed you've always had a talent for math.

90
00:08:33,952 --> 00:08:37,559
Don't waste your chance. Study hard.

91
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:44,179
Use this time to really think
about your future plans.

92
00:08:45,019 --> 00:08:49,860
Ruo Cheng, I've actually already decided.

93
00:08:49,860 --> 00:08:51,779
Good to hear.

94
00:08:51,779 --> 00:08:57,320
I want... I want to return to Hong Yang.

95
00:08:57,320 --> 00:09:00,100
Don't you want to study at Hong Kong University?

96
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:04,539
I've only studied here a year.
Haven't forgotten what I've learned yet.

97
00:09:04,539 --> 00:09:08,820
So going back to Hong Yang,
I could still get good grades.

98
00:09:08,820 --> 00:09:10,880
But you're studying finance now.

99
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:12,799
If you enter this industry in the future,

100
00:09:12,799 --> 00:09:17,640
having Hong Kong education background
gives you an edge, right?

101
00:09:18,519 --> 00:09:22,940
Ruo Cheng, I understand Qiao Xi's intentions.

102
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:29,920
Think about it. If he stays here,
he'll be apart from Cherry for three more years.

103
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:37,320
Alright, getting Ruo Cheng home for dinner today
took me convincing the doctor endlessly.

104
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,100
We need to take him back soon.

105
00:09:39,100 --> 00:09:43,500
Let's not discuss
Qiao Xi's crucial studies during dinner.

106
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,899
- Let's eat.
- Eat.

107
00:09:44,899 --> 00:09:45,899
Let's eat first.

108
00:09:45,899 --> 00:09:47,379
Qiao Xi, listen to me.

109
00:09:47,379 --> 00:09:49,500
Eat.

110
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:55,419
I know emotions matter sometimes,

111
00:09:55,419 --> 00:10:00,139
but what's more important
than feelings is acting on them.

112
00:10:00,139 --> 00:10:06,559
Don't just focus on the present.
Consider your future, right?

113
00:10:06,559 --> 00:10:10,440
Now nothing I say matters. You won't listen.

114
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,360
No heavy talks during meals.

115
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,500
Fine. Let's eat.

116
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,380
Cherry, eat up.

117
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:19,120
Cheers.

118
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,700
Be happy.

119
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:23,799
Cheer up.

120
00:10:23,799 --> 00:10:26,679
Eat whatever you like.

121
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:28,460
I... I can understand a little.

122
00:10:28,460 --> 00:10:31,700
When I was little, I loved watching
The Return of the Condor Heroes with my parents.

123
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:35,120
I adored Little Dragon Maiden in that series.

124
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,600
Are you saying I look like her?

125
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,480
- Yes. Many say that.
- Really?

126
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:40,860
Lots of people think so.

127
00:10:40,860 --> 00:10:43,620
No wonder I felt an instant connection
when I met Ya Lin.

128
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:46,540
Exactly. I'm so lucky to have married a fairy.

129
00:10:48,779 --> 00:10:55,120
You're really planning
to retake the college entrance exam?

130
00:10:57,139 --> 00:11:03,620
I've already made you wait two years.
I can't idle away another three.

131
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:11,539
But you're already at HKU. Why restart?

132
00:11:11,539 --> 00:11:14,620
Retaking the exam will be stressful.

133
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:23,179
Cherry, remember what I told you
in Hong Yang after your exams?

134
00:11:26,259 --> 00:11:34,179
I said I wanted to attend college, study
in libraries, and eat at cafeterias with you.

135
00:11:34,179 --> 00:11:39,799
Even if you attend a college in Hong Yang,
we'd only have one year together.

136
00:11:39,799 --> 00:11:44,859
That's okay. I'll take any chance, even a year.

137
00:11:55,779 --> 00:12:01,079
Your 18th birthday gift was getting kitchenware?

138
00:12:01,919 --> 00:12:06,159
Yes. I always enjoyed cooking.

139
00:12:06,159 --> 00:12:09,759
But I've been too busy these past two years.

140
00:12:09,759 --> 00:12:12,379
Now that Ruo Cheng's better,

141
00:12:12,379 --> 00:12:15,480
I want to revive this hobby.

142
00:12:15,480 --> 00:12:20,120
Don't save money for me.
I've earned plenty tutoring.

143
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:24,059
We have contest prize money too.
You could ask for nicer things.

144
00:12:25,419 --> 00:12:26,879
How about this?

145
00:12:26,879 --> 00:12:32,159
You said Ya Lin thinks lipstick and heels
mark a girl's maturity.

146
00:12:32,159 --> 00:12:36,159
Ask Ruo Cheng what marks a boy's maturity.

147
00:12:36,159 --> 00:12:40,059
I could buy you suits or leather shoes.

148
00:12:40,059 --> 00:12:41,320
You'd look handsome in them.

149
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:44,580
I don't want suits or shoes.

150
00:12:44,580 --> 00:12:52,000
Real maturity for boys
is owning a full kitchenware set.

151
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,259
Seriously?

152
00:12:53,259 --> 00:13:01,559
Really. Also, you're leaving tomorrow.
I want to cook for you.

153
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:15,159
Alright, but what if you mess up this grand plan?

154
00:13:15,159 --> 00:13:17,220
You haven't cooked in two years.

155
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:20,879
Underestimate me? My brain's full of recipes.

156
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:24,019
Why memorize recipes if you don't cook?

157
00:13:24,019 --> 00:13:28,200
You wouldn't get it. They fuel my daydreams.

158
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,020
Daydream fuel?

159
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:36,399
Stare at recipes when hungry?

160
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:38,199
No.

161
00:13:39,440 --> 00:13:46,439
You said you imagine alternate-reality versions
of me when apart.

162
00:13:47,879 --> 00:13:49,679
Me too.

163
00:13:50,659 --> 00:13:57,000
I imagine different versions of us
when you're not by my side.

164
00:13:58,679 --> 00:14:06,459
In that world, we're always together.
I cook you countless meals.

165
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:18,600
Well, try harder. I grew up on Ms. Juan's cooking.

166
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:21,939
I won't eat if it's bad.

167
00:14:23,519 --> 00:14:26,719
Surpassing Ms. Juan's impossible.

168
00:14:27,379 --> 00:14:31,439
But I'll practice until you want my cooking.

169
00:14:57,259 --> 00:14:59,960
Remember what I told you?

170
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:05,559
Pick oranges with round, pretty navels.
They're sweeter. Got it?

171
00:15:05,559 --> 00:15:07,359
Noted.

172
00:15:08,639 --> 00:15:10,540
Wait. Look at this.

173
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:21,919
Cherry, doesn't it feel
like we've lived this way forever?

174
00:15:21,919 --> 00:15:27,519
Obviously! We grew up together.

175
00:15:27,519 --> 00:15:31,980
You mooched meals at my house daily.
Couldn't shoo you away.

176
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:37,519
But grocery shopping together,
planning dinner, that's new.

177
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:43,280
It just feels familiar to me.
Like we've done this countless times.

178
00:15:44,639 --> 00:15:50,299
Jiang Qiao Xi, I never realized
you're such a quiet daydreamer.

179
00:15:50,299 --> 00:15:54,200
Your mind's full of whimsical ideas.

180
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,319
But reality's better than my imagination.

181
00:15:58,019 --> 00:16:01,780
I want to make all those daydreams real.

182
00:16:02,419 --> 00:16:03,899
Get this.

183
00:16:03,899 --> 00:16:05,699
Okay.

184
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:17,159
Cherry, I... I won't make you wait long.

185
00:16:17,159 --> 00:16:22,540
Even if I stay at HKU,
I'll return to Hong Yang quickly to find you.

186
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:30,432
Promise me, come running back soon.

187
00:16:57,330 --> 00:17:00,979
You really want to buy it?

188
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:05,300
Just buy it.

189
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:14,379
You think I don't know?

190
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:22,240
It's fine. I understand.

191
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,639
Are... are you serious?

192
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:34,760
I saw them.

193
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:40,839
Cigarettes on your windowsill. You smoke, right?

194
00:17:41,759 --> 00:17:44,579
It's okay. My dad smoked too.

195
00:17:44,579 --> 00:17:48,720
He quit for my mom using gum.

196
00:17:54,539 --> 00:17:57,640
I don't smoke much. I can quit soon.

197
00:17:57,640 --> 00:18:00,480
This should be good, or...?

198
