228
00:20:26,339 --> 00:20:30,180
Are you two being this innocent
even when you're dating each other?

229
00:20:33,779 --> 00:20:36,500
Do you want to grab dinner together later?

230
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,300
Sure.

231
00:20:44,460 --> 00:20:46,000
Yin.

232
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:52,040
You brat! I've been good to you for nothing?
You won't even cook a meal for me?

233
00:20:52,660 --> 00:20:59,039
Yin, tell me how he's been these past two years.

234
00:20:59,039 --> 00:21:00,980
You really want to know?

235
00:21:00,980 --> 00:21:03,240
I'm scared you'll cry.
He had it rough. No, better not.

236
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:08,300
I don't believe you can make me cry.
I've got a high threshold for tears. Go ahead.

237
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:13,940
Wait, don't fall for her act. She cries easily.

238
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,079
So are we telling it or not?

239
00:21:16,079 --> 00:21:17,099
We're telling it.

240
00:21:17,099 --> 00:21:19,599
Let me tell you how clueless
he was when he first arrived.

241
00:21:19,599 --> 00:21:22,119
He thought everything here was super complicated.

242
00:21:22,119 --> 00:21:25,099
Tried to act tough by putting on this macho front.

243
00:21:25,099 --> 00:21:29,039
The scar on his head was so tiny
you needed a magnifying glass to see it.

244
00:21:29,039 --> 00:21:33,380
Every day he'd flip his hair to show that scar,
thinking it made him look intimidating.

245
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:34,599
Why are you spilling everything?

246
00:21:34,599 --> 00:21:37,339
He looked absolutely ridiculous doing that.

247
00:21:37,339 --> 00:21:39,779
When I first saw you, I couldn't stand you.

248
00:21:39,779 --> 00:21:43,619
Barely scraping together rent money
but acting all high and mighty.

249
00:21:43,619 --> 00:21:48,880
If my dad hadn't taken a liking to you,
I'd have kicked you out on the spot.

250
00:21:48,880 --> 00:21:52,980
See how kind Yin is?
Even when you were putting on airs back then.

251
00:21:52,980 --> 00:21:55,079
He still took you in and treated you well.

252
00:21:55,079 --> 00:21:57,660
I wasn't putting on airs!
Don't listen to his nonsense.

253
00:21:57,660 --> 00:21:59,960
Cherry, I'm the landlord here.

254
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:04,400
Shouldn't a landlord evict tenants
who can't pay rent?

255
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:07,599
I helped him not because of that.

256
00:22:10,279 --> 00:22:12,139
Then why?

257
00:22:15,339 --> 00:22:20,119
Don't they say men can't bear to see women cry?

258
00:22:20,119 --> 00:22:23,500
Actually, men can't stand
seeing other men cry even more.

259
00:22:24,119 --> 00:22:28,700
One night he was watching Titanic and cried.

260
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:31,279
Right, Titanic's a real tearjerker.

261
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:37,299
But most people cry
when Rose sees Jack sinking. Not him.

262
00:22:37,299 --> 00:22:43,599
He cried when Rose and Jack
promised each other a beautiful life together.

263
00:22:43,599 --> 00:22:49,779
That's the most hopeful part,
yet he sobbed like a mess.

264
00:22:49,779 --> 00:22:55,680
That's when I realized
this kid was actually pitiful.

265
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:01,200
So I figured I'd look after him in my free time.

266
00:23:06,380 --> 00:23:13,720
Yin, I'll toast you. Thank you
for taking care of Jiang Qiao Xi these years.

267
00:23:14,619 --> 00:23:16,419
No need.

268
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:22,619
Don't spit it out!

269
00:23:22,619 --> 00:23:26,180
My reserve whiskey isn't cheap.

270
00:23:26,180 --> 00:23:28,000
Well? How is it?

271
00:23:29,700 --> 00:23:31,859
So hot!

272
00:23:31,859 --> 00:23:32,859
Stop drinking.

273
00:23:32,859 --> 00:23:35,160
- Burning up.
- It's too hot, right?

274
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,940
Bottoms up.

275
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:39,040
I'll add some ice.

276
00:23:42,299 --> 00:23:48,180
Yin, I've tried lots of fine drinks in Hong Kong.

277
00:23:48,180 --> 00:23:53,039
Had wine with Jiang Qiao Xi's sister-in-law,
and now your whiskey.

278
00:23:53,039 --> 00:23:55,019
All top-shelf stuff, really expensive.

279
00:23:55,019 --> 00:24:00,200
But honestly, I just can't acquire
the taste. Don't like it.

280
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:02,819
Why do you all love alcohol so much?

281
00:24:02,819 --> 00:24:06,000
Nobody's born liking alcohol.

282
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,420
I drink out of necessity.

283
00:24:09,420 --> 00:24:14,079
Not everyone's like Vincent,
having a sweet girl like you to care for him.

284
00:24:14,079 --> 00:24:18,640
I have nobody. That's why I drink.

285
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:22,780
Who believes that?
Jiang Qiao Xi says you're a player.

286
00:24:25,819 --> 00:24:29,099
That's just acting for
the occasion. Doesn't count.

287
00:24:30,619 --> 00:24:35,839
I treat them badly, they treat me
badly too. Fair's fair.

288
00:24:39,140 --> 00:24:40,940
Eat.

289
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:49,400
Don't... don't be sad.
You'll definitely meet someone...

290
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:54,059
Stop pitying him.
You actually believe his stories?

291
00:24:54,059 --> 00:24:58,200
He owns this building and land in Lok Ma Chau.

292
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:01,300
He stays up all night counting property deeds.

293
00:25:02,039 --> 00:25:10,380
You don't get it. Pretty clouds scatter easily,
